{"ID":270281, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"281\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs280.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs282.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 281<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">ence to destroy the children that I was blessing, and I strove with all the faith and spirit<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span> that I had\n  to seal upon them a blessing<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> that would secure their lives upon the earth; and so much virtue went\n  out of me<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> into the children, that I became weak, from which I have not yet recovered; and I referred\n  to the case of the woman touching the hem of the garment of Jesus. (Luke, 8th chapter.)<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> The virtue\n  here referred to is the spirit of life;<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> and a man who exercises great faith<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> in administering to the\n  sick,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> blessing little children,<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> or confirming,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> is liable to become weakened.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> (March 14, 1843.)\n  DHC 5:303.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110017\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110017)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110017)\">1 Tim. 4:12<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116052\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116052)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116052)\">D&amp;C 124:124<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108463\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108463)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108463)\">Luke 6:19<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"fo